						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Hero-stone set up in the compound of the Kallēśvara Temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>Śubhatuṅga (Kṛishṇa II)—A.D. 878-79.</p>						

						<p>The record seems to refer to the date <hi rend="bold">[Śaka] 800.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription seems to state that a certain Nāgati, son of Duggatigauḍa died in a cattle-raid, at <hi rend="bold">Sālatti.</hi> Makara-Ijja was the governor.</p>						

